OUR VISION We think everybody should have the opportunity to travel the world. We imagine a planet where our differences don't divide us, where our dissimilarities are a source of inspiration and development, not xenophobia and prejudice. We hope to achieve our dream of a diversified world by making travel cheaper and encouraging each of us to stay curious and be progressive.   OUR MISSION Our mission at Airporia is to empower you to make confident decisions when purchasing flights, hotels, and car rentals. We see our site as more than just an excellent search tool; it takes you one step closer to where you need to be. ABOUT THE FOUNDER  Nasib Gul founded Airporia in 2021. His business is based in Michigan, where he resides with his family. Nasib enjoys traveling and staying active, and this website is his way to share that joy with everyone on earth. column8: The LOKI team brought together a mixture of industry innovators and creative thinkers to craft a truly original drinking experience. Consumers want to immerse themselves in memorable moments, but often crave alternatives to alcohol. Cannabis products have become more popular and a wide variety of new pioneering cannabis-based options continue to change the landscape of nightlife and social gatherings. LOKI blends these consumer trends and offers a completely new way to enjoy the night. A true innovation in drinking. With only a few sips, you can enhance any moment. As knowledge, research, and complexity around the marijuana industry evolves, new discoveries about the active ingredients and their unique characteristics are constantly being discovered. LOKI's unique ingredient is Delta-8-THC, which is one of the lesser-known natural elements of the cannabis plant. It differs from its more commonly known relative Delta-9-THC by a slight variation in molecular structure. Most cannabis users experience the potent effects of Delta-9, as it makes up the majority of the plant's THC presence. However, by using an extraction method, LOKI can take the more isolated and rarer Delta-8 and offer a cleaner overall experience. Delta-8 offers consumers a far lower psychotropic potency, while still giving them the ability to immerse in prolonged and enjoyable moments. No hangover, no paranoia, no lack of clarity.

column8: Traditional credit scoring is statistically less inclusive for minorities, immigrants and younger people, lacking a long credit history. This happens to overlap with the majority of renters, particularly in Affordable Housing. Matrix uses real time data and produces an “ability to pay” score. Using a variety of factors, including Assets, Income and Previous Rental History, the result is more inclusive scoring that gives property managers insights into the full financial profile of a prospective tenant. Matrix removes the potential for Source of Income discrimination, taking the subsidy into consideration and automating the underwriting process. On the back end, today’s processing time for Affordable Housing is approximately 36 days. This leads to compounding losses for property managers, making public housing acceptance simply not an option for many landlords. Matrix streamlines the acceptance process and shortens it by up to 50%, helping more owners make their properties available to affordable housing and get leased up faster.

column8: REALTIME PREDICTIVE INSIGHTS FOR HEDGE FUNDS: Simple answers to high-value questions. Investors seek fundamental insights into the companies they invest in. They can gain a competitive advantage by licensing proprietary information that only a limited number of funds can find and afford. To build these high-value datasets, we strategically place cameras/sensors to collect images/data of business activities that map to key company performance insights. We can process that data with AI (Computer Vision/Machine Learning) to generate unique insights into high-value questions for Hedge Funds and other asset managers.  Specifically, in our first two datasets we collect highly accurate and precise counts of every vehicle (Model Y or now Cybertruck) produced by Tesla at the GigaTexas factory and all four models (S, X, 3, and Y) vehicles produced at Fremont, CA. We license this data to hedge funds seeking an information advantage for trading equities.  Investors call this type of information Alternative Data or External Data because it's not published or directly sanctioned by the companies we observe. It is often built through innovative technology from unconventional sources. As we scale up, we expect to have numerous high-valued locations. We are hiring in several areas, DM me directly.

column8: Unexpected medical care is stressful enough for patients and healthcare providers, so Urgently Health strives to streamline and simplify the last-minute, unplanned medical process. Our mobile application (Urgently Health), available for both Apple and Android devices, allows patients to discover local, available, medical care facilities based on their specific medical needs, along with estimated wait times so they can be seen and treated as soon as possible. The App also allows patients to browse providers based on specialties and services offered, as well as by insurances accepted. This way, patients avoid surprises when arriving at the front desk. Additional patient benefits include: -- Filling out paperwork before arriving at urgent care facilities, hospitals, and other walk-in medical providers -- Seeing medical care facility information, including locations, hours of operation, estimated wait times, contact information, specialties and services offered, and insurances accepted -- Storage of their medical forms, medical history, pre-existing conditions, etc. -- Reduction of wait times in hospitals, clinics, emergency rooms, and other medical care providers -- Reduction of stress associated with unplanned, last-minute care and medical emergencies Urgently Health also notifies the hospital or clinic a patient chooses that they are on their way to them, providing healthcare facilities with an approximate travel time. This feature allows providers to expect patients and better prepare for their arrival before they get there. This is vitally important during emergencies where mere minutes can make a difference! Our accompanying Web Platform allows hospitals and clinics who accept walk-in patients to process them more effectively and with less confusion than in the past. When healthcare facilities use our Platform, they expand their visibility and streamline their day-to-day operations. This, in turn, increases their preparedness and allows them to discover and overcome bottlenecks, leading to more effective and efficient service, greater patient satisfaction and retention, and decreased costs. With patient information on-hand before they arrive, providers can assign severity, pre-triage, and verify information before their patients arrive. The Platform also provides healthcare administrators with statistics such as hot-times, most common ailments, and historical wait-times to mitigate over and under-staffing and ensure preparation.

column8: Nile is a digital platform that makes it easy for conscientious online shoppers and Black-owned ecommerce brands to connect online. Users can employ advanced filtering options to search and browse thousands of Black e-commerce brands on our site, and brands can reach their target audiences with greater ease. The problem Nile solves is two-sided. For conscientious consumers, there is a growing demand to support Black-owned businesses in all aspects, particularly when shopping online. Yet, information about Black brands is disjointed and siloed. Plainly speaking, it’s harder to buy Black than it is to buy from Amazon, so where do consumers end up shopping online? Amazon.  For Black ecommerce brands, the problem is even more pressing. Amongst the vast retail noise on the internet, they can’t find their target customers. Our platform aggregates information about Black brands to make it easy for consumers to find them, and to make it easy for brands to market to interested buyers. Without Nile, users spend more time searching for Black brands on search engines or directories that are focused on local businesses and services, and businesses have a harder time reaching a prime (inter)national audience for their products.

Imagine how much it turns our world upside down when we’ve received a major diagnosis like cancer, COVID, diabetes, COPD, a heart attack, or have had an accidental injury. There is often no time to digest what has happened and grieve for the loss of the old normal. Beyond that, a patient and their support group now must become expert project managers and level-up on their medical knowledge. If you’ve been in this situation or supported someone who is, you know it’s completely overwhelming.  Friends and family are concerned, and feel bad about the interruptions it causes when they reach out to ask for help.  Some friends and family simply stop reaching out, not knowing what to say or do. All of them care, and know that their loved one can’t have 75 conversations a day while during normal times, much less with the additional burden of recovery.  That’s why we created ReplyAll Health. We have experienced major health issues like cancer and COVID. We were desperate to keep our community updated and wanted to be sure they could stay informed without creating an extra burden.  One message: Unlimited recipients Even “technophobes” love ReplyAll.  It’s as simple as sending one text. One text that goes to whoever wants to receive it, for as long as they want to receive it. Whether you have a small circle, or a village. No matter if they’re on Android or Apple. No matter if they’re a PhD in Computer Science or don’t know how to find a web browser. No log-ins. No sign-ups. No passwords. Nothing except one text number and one text message.
